   noaa logo NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE      Operations Manual
                                                     SILVER SPRING,
   MARYLAND 20910    Letter 3-90

   Date of Issue: July 26, 1990
   Effective Date: March 3, 1990

   In Reply Refer To: W/OM13                                    File With:
   D-38

   Subject: International Aviation In-Flight Advisories

   Reference(s): WSOM Chapter D-38, Transmittal Issuance 88-5 dated May
   27, 1988

   The Federal Aviation Administration has transferred a large (nonradar
   controlled) part of the San Juan Oceanic Flight Information Region
   (FIR) to the New York Oceanic FIR. As a result of that change, this
   OML:

   1     shifts the boundary between the Washington and Miami
   Meteorological Watch Offices' area of responsibility to 30 degrees
   north for international SIGMETs in accordance with the international
   aviation and satellite and high seas plans and

   2.    revises the area for which SIGMETs are issued with respect to the
   decreased size of the San Juan and increased size of the New York
   Oceanic FIRs.

   These changes are shown in the attachment and became effective March 3,
   1990,.at 0000 UTC.

   Elbert W. Friday, Jr. Assistant Administrator for Weather Services
